projectInfo.name: Missing Maps: Embu county, Kenya (2) - with RapiD
projectInfo.shortDescription:
MSF is supporting health centres in Embu County in Kenya to develop a model of care for Non Communicable Diseases such as diabetes or epilepsy. In order to have a good understanding of the area of interest of the project, it would be valuable to have a high detailed map of the county. 

This map would help the team to know the accessibility to the health facilities (as it is planned to support more next year) as well as their catchment area. The OpenStreetMap community can help by digitalizing the roads and main landmarks and the teams on site will collect more precise information such as villages names or health facilities locations.

projectInfo.instructions:
Imagery
========================
Please use **Maxar Imagery** in this task.

Roads
=========================
This task is set up with the [RapiD editor](https://mapwith.ai/). This editor allows you to add AI predicted features with one click. However, verification of the data by humans is needed! **Do not just accept the automatically detected features and their tags, please do ensure proper alignment, connection and tagging of the road before adding.**

Follow next steps:

1. Zoom in on a pink AI road.
2. Select the pink AI road, this allows you to see the road segment better.
3. Examine the full road segment. Hitting **Shift R** on your keyboard allows you to switch on and off the pink AI data. 
4. If the road does not align correctly with he imagery, click on **Remove this feature**. If the road aligns (almost) correctly with the imagery, click on **Use this feature**
5. If the road does not fully align with the imagery adapt the shape of the road so it aligns correctly. 
5. Check if the tag of your road is correct. You'll see the tag of the road at the top of the left window. If the tag is wrong, do change it by clicking on it and search for the right type of road according your judgement. 

The following tags for roads should be used: 
- **Minor/Unclassified Road** (is *highway=unclassified* in JOSM) for roads connecting villages and hamlets with each other.
- **Residential Road** (is *highway=residential* in JOSM) inside towns and villages.
- **Unmaintained Track Road** (is *highway=track* in JOSM) for roads which connect fields and farmland or are leading just to rivers and ponds.
- **Path** (is *highway=path* in JOSM) for roads too narrow for a 4-wheel drive vehicle to pass.

See [Highway East Africa Tagging Guidelines](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/East_Africa_Tagging_Guidelines) for more advice on tagging roads in East Africa.

If you see residential roads or minor/unclassified roads that are not detected by AI, please do map them as well. For tracks and paths this is not needed. 

If you would like to use the **JOSM editor**, you can download the **mapwithai plugin**. Once downloaded, check the Data tab in JOSM to download and add the AI detected data.


Waterways
=========================
To map a waterway **draw a line** and add the correct tag.  The direction of the line should be downstream - in the direction that the river flows. The most important thing is to maintain consistency in the water network. **Every waterway should connect to another one.**

Use **Water Features**: 
- **River** (is *waterway=river* in JOSM) for large waterways (<10m).
- **Stream** (is *waterway=stream* in JOSM) for small waterways (>10m).

For small waterways, a line along its path is sufficient, but when a waterway becomes wide enough, mapping the area it flows through as *water=riverbank* is desired in addition. Find [here](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tag:waterway%3Driverbank) how to map this.

Water surfaces
=========================
To map a water surface like a lake or pond, **draw an area** and add the correct tag. 

Use **Water Features**:
- **Water** (is *natural=water* in JOSM).

If a shape already exists, but does not encompass the whole water surface, please adjust the boundary accordingly.
